<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4326678>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 14. Adeonellopsis gemina n. sp.: A. Profile of vicarious avicularia in a branch axil (NIWA 146078). B. Ephebic autozooids showing adventitious avicularia and their disposition in relation to sunken spiramina (NIWA 146078). C. Autozooidal spiramen (NIWA 146095). D. Fossil fragment (NIWA 146150), all zooids with much secondary calcification (Pleistocene). E. Spiramen wholly sunken proximal to suboral avicularium. F. Autozooidal peristomial orifice of Recent specimen with denticulation of inner rim (NIWA 146074). G. Internal view of spiramen and orifice with denticulated rim (Pleistocene). H. Old thickly calcified isolated stem with regenerative new growth from its proximal end; the arrows indicate growth direction (NIWA 146082). Scalebars: A, B, 500 μm; C, 30 μm; D, 1 mm; E, 100 μm; F, G, 50 μm; H, 2 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4326678/files/figure.png" .

